jenny-may clarkson (née coffin; 9 april 1974 in te kuiti, new zealand) is a new zealand netball player and sports commentator. coffin previously played for the silver ferns, new zealand's national netball team, for which she was the vice-captain in 2001. she also played for the waikato bay of plenty magic in the national bank cup between 1998–2004 and the auckland diamonds in 2007; she also played one season in the anz championship in 2008 for the southern steel, and is signed to play with the northern mystics in 2010. coffin is currently a sports commentator and news presenter for tvnz and māori television.